 the post-2008 global economic crisis and the period of austerity, this volume draws together edited chapters from leading scholars engaged in the debate and will be equally suitable for academics and other researchers studying international and comparative social policy, as well as upper level undergraduate and postgraduate students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aEconomic policy. 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009. 0aSocial policy. 0aWelfare state. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aFarnsworth, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarnsworth, Kevin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHill, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrving, Zoë, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrving, Zoë, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJessop, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcBride, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinnite, Lorraine C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiven, Frances Fox, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpoehr, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhitfield, Dexter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311119642840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447319139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447319139/original  a978-3-11-119642-8  Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles